      "message": "Issue: The keyword modification adds navigation back to overview page, but this may cause issues if the keyword is called multiple times or from different contexts.\n\nProblem:\n\nThe navigation back to overview is added inside the IF block for PowerOn state\nThis creates an asymmetry: PowerOn state navigates back, PowerOff state doesn\u0027t\nIf this keyword is called in a sequence, the navigation state becomes unpredictable\n\n\nOption : Add navigation for both states (consistent behavior)\n\n    IF  \u0027${power_value}\u0027 !\u003d \u0027Not available\u0027\n        Click Element  ${xpath_power_heading}\n        Wait Until Page Contains Element  ${xpath_power_heading}  timeout\u003d30\n        ${power_tab_value}\u003d  Get Text  ${xpath_power_tab_power_consumption}\n        Should Be Equal As Strings  ${power_value}  ${power_tab_value}\n        Click Element  ${xpath_overview_menu}\n        Wait Until Page Contains Element  ${xpath_overview_page_header}\n        Wait Until Element Is Not Visible   ${xpath_page_loading_progress_bar}  timeout\u003d30\n    ELSE\n        Should Be Equal As Strings  ${power_value}  Not available\n        # Navigate back to overview for consistency\n        Click Element  ${xpath_overview_menu}\n        Wait Until Page Contains Element  ${xpath_overview_page_header}\n        Wait Until Element Is Not Visible   ${xpath_page_loading_progress_bar}  timeout\u003d30\n    END",
